The ulnae in the hypodigm are highly incomplete (
fig. 13A–I
). Even so, the size contrast between both MNHNCu 76.1014 and 76.1017 on the one hand and MNHNCu 76.1016 on the other is quite noticeable, the former being larger for given linear measurements by,20–25%. MNHNCu 76.1014 and 76.1017 are from opposite sides of the body, but in size they are very similar and quite possibly represent the same animal.
